## 6. Pyramid of Pain positioning

**Declared level: TTPs**

An adversary performing classical DLL injection cannot evade this hunt without abandoning
the technique entirely. The three steps ‚Äî write memory into a remote process, create a thread
in that process, observe a module load in that process ‚Äî are not optional implementation
details. They are what the technique is. The specific DLL name changes; the specific target
process changes; the tooling changes between campaigns. None of these changes affects
detection because none of them appears as a filter in the query. The query filters on the
API call sequence, not on any artifact the adversary can rotate cheaply. This is the
operational meaning of "TTP-level detection" on the Pyramid of Pain.

